Dear [Candidate Name],

Offer of Internship
We are pleased to offer you the position of AI Intern at Omninuera. This letter summarizes the terms and conditions of your internship. Please review the information carefully. This offer is subject to legal compliance review.

Position and Title
- Title: AI Intern
- Department: [Department or Team]
- Location: Remote (Company headquarters: Omninuera, Bengaluru, India)
- Reporting to: [Reporting Manager]

Start Date and Duration
- Start Date: [Start Date]
- Duration: 3 months (approximately [Start Date] to [End Date], exact end date to be confirmed)
- This internship is for a fixed-term period and will automatically end at the conclusion of the 3-month term unless otherwise extended in writing by Omninuera.

Stipend and Payment Schedule
- Stipend: INR 10,000 (Indian Rupees Ten Thousand) per month.
- Payment Schedule: Stipend will be paid monthly in arrears via bank transfer to the account details you provide. Payments will be made on or before [Payment Day — e.g., 7th] of the following month. Please provide necessary bank details and tax documentation prior to your start date.
- No additional benefits (such as medical insurance, paid leave, or gratuity) are included unless expressly set out in a separate written agreement.

Work Arrangement and Expectations
- Work Arrangement: Completely remote. You are expected to perform duties from your remote location.
- Company Location (for records): Omninuera, Bengaluru, India.
- Time Zone and Working Hours: Expected working hours are [e.g., 10:00 AM — 6:00 PM IST] (India Standard Time, UTC+05:30), Monday through Friday. Some flexibility is permitted upon discussion with your reporting manager, but you are expected to be available for scheduled team meetings and collaboration within core hours [e.g., 11:00 AM — 4:00 PM IST]. Please discuss any exceptions with [Reporting Manager].
- Communication and Tools: You will be required to use company-approved communication tools (e.g., email, Slack, Zoom) and collaboration platforms. You must maintain reliable internet connectivity and ensure a suitable remote work environment.

Probation and Termination
- Probation: Your performance will be reviewed during the internship. While this is a short-term fixed-duration internship, there will be ongoing performance feedback.
- Termination: Either party may terminate this internship with seven (7) days’ written notice. Omninuera may terminate the internship immediately for cause, including but not limited to breach of company policies, misconduct, or unsatisfactory performance.

Confidentiality and Intellectual Property
- Confidentiality: During the course of your internship and thereafter, you must maintain the confidentiality of Omninuera’s confidential and proprietary information. You will be required to sign the company’s Confidentiality Agreement prior to or on your start date.
- Intellectual Property Assignment: Any work product, inventions, developments, designs, code, documentation, or other materials created by you in the scope of your internship shall be the exclusive property of Omninuera. You will be required to sign an IP Assignment Agreement to assign all rights in such work products to Omninuera.

Compliance with Company Policies
- You agree to comply with all Omninuera policies, including but not limited to data protection, acceptable use, information security, remote work policies, and any other applicable internal policies. Policies will be provided as part of onboarding.

Background Check and Eligibility
- Contingency: This offer is contingent upon successful completion of any background checks and verification of eligibility to intern (including identity and educational verification). Please provide the documents requested by HR to facilitate this process.
- If adverse information arises from background verification, Omninuera reserves the right to withdraw or rescind this offer.

Onboarding Steps
To complete your onboarding, please:
1. Sign and return this offer letter by [Offer Expiration Date: e.g., 7 days from receipt].
2. Complete pre-employment forms and provide required identity, educational, and bank documents.
3. Complete and sign the Confidentiality and IP Assignment documents provided by HR.
4. Attend an onboarding/orientation meeting scheduled with [Reporting Manager] on your first day.
5. Provide any equipment or tooling requirements in advance; Omninuera will inform you of company-provided tools or access credentials where applicable.

Acceptance Instructions
To accept this offer:
- Sign below and return a scanned copy by email to HR at [HR Email Address] by [Offer Expiration Date].
- Alternatively, reply via email stating your acceptance with an electronic signature and the date.

Accepted and agreed:

